<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,1823,2092]" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,463,1823,1849]" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">Distribution and habitat:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[464,663,1823,1849]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peplus">
<emphasis box="[464,663,1823,1849]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">Euphorbia peplus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in the Mediterranean region, Europe and temperate Asia, being introduced and naturalized as a weed in temperate, subtropical and tropical regions around the world. In the State of 
<collectingRegion box="[136,249,1892,1918]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
the species occurs in disturbed areas.
</paragraph>
